! This is a sample input of gradient calculation for optimized Be2.
! The parameter used in this calculation is described in the following
! literature:
!   Takagi, H.; Koike, F.; Nakamura, N.; Sakaue, H. A.; Sawada, K.; Goto, M.;
!   Kato, D.; Ashikawa, N.; Nishimura, Y.; Saito, J.; Yokogawa, D.;
!   Chou, C.-P.; Witek, H.-A.; Irle, S. J. Plasma Fusion Res. 2013, 89, 583-598.
! Although the journal is in Japanese , the computational part is written in
! English.
!
! This calculation corresponds to SCC-DFTB (DFTB2), and iterative SCF
! calculation is performed until it converges.
!
! The total energy is -0.8628099171 (Hartree) after 3 SCF cycles,
! and nuclear energy is 0.0438123135.
! The maximum and RMS gradients must be less than 1.0d-08.
!
! The bond length shown in the paper above is 2.097 (Parameter 1).
!
! Disclaimer: these parameters are provided so that the correctness of
! the DFTB code in GAMESS can be tested. For production DFTB runs,
! please obtain parameters from the official site www.dftb.org. 
!
! You will have to edit the path below in $DFTBSK to run this input.
!
! Do not run DFTB in parallel (except FMO-DFTB, see exam04.inp)! 
!
! This file was provided by Yoshio Nishimoto and Stephan Irle,
! and the parameters were generated by Yoshifumi Nishimura (Nagoya U., Japan). 
!
 $CONTRL RUNTYP=GRADIENT NPRINT=-5 $END
 $SYSTEM MWORDS=40 $END
 $SCF CONV=1.0D-12 $END
 $BASIS GBASIS=DFTB $END
 $DFTB NDFTB=2 $END
!  --- !!!! modify the path below !!!! ---
 $DFTBSK
   Be Be "/usr/local/dftb/parameters/Be-Be.spl"
 $END
 $DATA
 Optimized Be2
 C1 
 BE          4.0   0.0000000000   0.0000000000   0.0000000000
 BE          4.0   2.0965676508   0.0000000000   0.0000000000
 $END

! TRAVIS-CI SMALL

